jobs.description:
1. Khảo sát, nghiên cứu, làm rõ sản phẩm đáp ứng yêu cầu khách hàng;
2. Tìm kiếm nhà cung cấp đáp ứng yêu cầu;
3. Chuẩn bị các hồ sơ thầu cho phần hồ sơ kỹ thuật, hồ sơ năng lực kỹ thuật;
4. Soạn thảo, kiểm tra và tư vấn các vấn đề liên quan đến điều kiện và điều khoản của các hợp đồng phần kỹ thuật;
5. Thực hiện, kiểm tra và giám sát các công việc kỹ thuật và pháp lý kỹ thuật theo yêu cầu của HĐ (phần liên quan đến kỹ thuật, tài liệu kỹ thuật…);
6. Giám sát, kiểm tra các thiết kế từ bộ phận thiết kế (trong và ngoài công ty) trước khi chuyển đến khách hàng phê duyệt tài liệu thiết kế;
7. Kiểm tra các hợp đồng mua hàng (phần kỹ thuật, tài liệu kỹ thuật…);
8. Phụ trách việc thiết kế các hệ thống trong phạm vi cung cấp của công ty khi có sự phân công của TP;
9. Kiểm tra thiết kế của nhà cung cấp/ đơn vị thiết kế bên ngoài dựa trên các yêu cầu kỹ thuật của gói thầu/ dự án theo yêu cầu của Khách hàng.

•	Developing a solid and trusting relationship between major key accounts and Würth business units located in Vietnam and globally around the world; 
•	 Expending relationships and business scope with existing Key Accounts and acquisition of new Key Accounts 
•	Build-Up and management of a pipeline and a potential oriented sales approach in order to reach individual and company sales, growth and gross profit targets 
•	Assisting in the resolution of key account issues and complaints, 
•	Developing a complete understanding of key account needs and a portfolio of solutions for such needs; 
•	Anticipating changes in structures of the organization of Key Accounts and management of the adjustment of Würth’s approach towards Key Accounts accordingly
•	Working with sales, logistics, purchasing, marketing and other stake holders within the company in order to ensure that client needs are met and exceeded while maintaining efforts on an economical level
•	Establish and engage in up-selling and/or cross-selling activities in order to maximize market share and profitability for both the customer as well as the Würth organization;
•	Planning and presenting reports on account progress, goals, and quarterly initiatives to share with team members, stakeholders, and possible use in future case studies or company trainings. 
•	Meeting all client needs and deliverables according to proposed timelines; 
•	Maintain and support 6-S principals and initiatives. 
•	Other tasks assigned by the company.

Your Tasks
In the business division Electronics, you will be working with the software development team for electronics control units.
- Design, develop & test product-specific software of automotive electronics module & system over the
entire product development cycle;
- Apply model-based development on a distributed embedded system;
- Work on SW-architecture, write, test and debug code according to software requirement specification and
the defined process;
- Discuss with customer about specific solution for electronics modules & system, including function
implementation and system interface;
- Complete software module test report and integration test report according to test result;
- Primarily responsible of software modules of HELLA products;
- Other job assigned by Department Manager.

jobs.requirements:
Qualifications
• Bachelor's degree in computer science / engineering or equivalent practical experience
• 5+ years of working experience in embedded linux environment
• 3+ years of working experience with the C++ programming language
• Preferred Experiences: Graphics, EGL, Wayland, webOS, unit test
• Good communication skill in English, mostly for the technical communication with the collaborating scrum teams
Benefits
• 13th month salary + incentive bonus (total remuneration package: up to 
• 16-month salary) with annual salary review; full paid in probation period;
• Health Premium insurance & accident insurance;
• Support fee to get TOEIC & Technical certifications;
• Join global technical exam and get valuable rewards;
• Oversea on-site & training opportunities;
• Staff trip, sporty clubs;
• Monthly budget for team building activities, etc.
• Attractive and competitive salary package (negotiable upon the interview);
• Support for lunch & transportation;
• 5 working days/ week: Mon~Fri with flexible working time and hybrid working;
• 12 days of annual leave & 8 additional days of company holiday

jobs.description:
Duties and responsibilities:
• Undertake duties and responsibilities instructed by the Project Manager;
• Check, inspect and monitor material quality;
• Review and ensure technical reports, test results to meet technical requirements;
• Monitor, take part in on-site tests and inspections;
• Check actual quality on site, promptly detect any violation of quality, and prepare reports (NCRs, CAR/PARs, SIs, Site minutes);
• Coordinate with and support to Site engineers in terms of quality; Coordinate with Supervisors;
• Prepare, distribution Quality Assurance / Quality Control documents;
• Take part in all activities of the Project in terms of quality.
• Stay up-to-date on relevant building codes and safety regulations.
• Assist with obtaining permits and other necessary documentation.
• Other duties as required.

